[SECURITY] Invalid cookie signature

A request arrived with a session cookie whose HMAC signature did not
verify against SECRET_KEY. The request was rejected before reaching
Redis or the database.

  Event  : {{ event_type }}
  When   : {{ when_str }}
  IP     : {{ ip or '(unknown)' }}
  Agent  : {{ user_agent or '(none)' }}
  Reason : {{ extra or '(none)' }}

Possible causes: an attacker probing forged cookies, OR a legitimate
client with a cookie issued before the latest SECRET_KEY rotation.

What to do:
  1. Cross-reference auth_events for repeat rows from this IP in the
     last hour.
  2. If the source IP is unfamiliar and clusters with other probes,
     add it to your edge blocklist.
  3. If you just rotated SECRET_KEY, the count will fall on its own.
